title: Grateful Dead Live at State Fairgrounds on 1980-09-06
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Far From Me, Little Red Rooster, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Promised Land

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance, Althea, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> The Wheel-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Sugar Magnolia, E:One More Saturday Night-> E: Brokedown Palace

Roy Bucanan then Levon Helm Opened

reviews.review_text:
Hot damn, this one's the shiznit I'll just address the sound quality here.

Out.....Freakin'.....Standing.

Vocals crisp, drums defined, guitars in your face and Phil...well, Phil is a thundering force that will make any money you may have put into a subwoofer become one of the best investments you will ever make.

Show itself is legendary for a reason.  I'll leave it at that.  A million thanks for finding this jewel.  I know many folks will never be swayed by an AUD, but this is about as good as it gets folks.
it's got the clap! fantastic recording and if the clapping was a bit lower this would be the clear 'winner' but in this collection of 80-09-06 I think the "Friend"24bit wins.

I think this one has the best sound Great show. Great feel. End of the summer, end of the tour, United States Bluez. Lots of songs (2 whole shows by some late era standards). Lots of well crafted and generous music. The definitive source is still to be found, but this one is better then most- and the clappies fit right in just fine by me.

Praise I was there! :-D Last minute road trip our of New Jersey. On the way up, I came down with a miserable head cold.

Despite that, it was a great, but very long show. It sounded just as good live, for sure. We made a weekend out if it; we were invited to a bluegrass festival the following day. LOL
